==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Culturist
<hw>Cul"tur*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
cultivator.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who is an advocate of culture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>culturists</qex>, by which term I mean not those who
esteem culture (as what intelligent man does not<?/) but those its
exclusive advocates who recommend it as the panacea for all the ills of
humanity, for its effects in cultivating the whole man.</q> <rj><qau>J.
C. Shairp</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cultus</ent>⟦br⟧
